modules.description: This module enables configuring and rendering interactive pie charts by defining data structure mappings, visual styling, and user interaction handlers. It operates on configuration objects that specify segment data, labels, tooltips, and effects, while supporting event callbacks for interactions like clicks or hovers. Typical use cases include visualizing categorical data distributions with customizable layouts, dynamic color schemes, and responsive tooltips or animations triggered by user actions.

This module enables creation of interactive pie charts through configuration-driven data mappings, styling options, and event handlers. It provides types for segment data, labels, tooltips, and visual effects, along with operations to define color schemes, layout parameters, and interaction callbacks. Users can render dynamic pie charts that respond to clicks or hovers with animations and tooltips, ideal for visualizing categorical data distributions. Example usage includes displaying survey results or budget allocations with customizable visuals and interactive feedback.
